```sql
WITH ranked_channels AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY customer_id ORDER BY attributed_at DESC) AS rn
    FROM customer_channels
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM ranked_channels
WHERE rn = 1
```

-- 02_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
```sql
WITH customer_primary_channel AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY customer_id ORDER BY attributed_at DESC) AS rn
    FROM customer_channels
),
transactions_with_attributes AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.store_id,
        t.amount,
        COALESCE(cpc.channel, 'Unknown') AS channel,
        COALESCE(s.city, 'Unknown') AS city
    FROM transactions t
    LEFT JOIN customer_primary_channel cpc
        ON t.customer_id = cpc.customer_id AND cpc.rn = 1
    LEFT JOIN stores s
        ON t.store_id = s.store_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM transactions_with_attributes
GROUP BY channel, city
ORDER BY total_revenue DESC
